# Handoff — Pack #5 (Knowledge Engine) Phase 3 complete

## What was done

**Phase 3 (Resilience) of Pack #5
(`knowledge-engine-json-store`) is
code-complete.** The on-disk `.index.json` is
now persisted; the adapter boots cleanly from a
fresh `tempfile::TempDir`, recovers from a
corrupt `.index.json` by rebuilding from the
on-disk `.md` files (with a `tracing::warn!`),
and cleans up any orphan `*.tmp.*` files left
behind by a crashed previous process. The
`content_tokens` lazy cache is now evicted on
every `store_information` (the Phase 2
"stale-cache" decision). The conformance suite
is extended with 4 audit-event tests and the
proptest round-trip suite covers all 9
Knowledge types (256 cases per type).

## Where the work landed

**New files:**

- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/src/index_file.rs` —
  the on-disk index format. `IndexFileV1` is
  `serde::Serialize` + `serde::Deserialize`,
  `schema_version: u32 = 1`, `topics:
  BTreeMap<String, TopicFile>` (with
  `record_count`, `first_record_at`,
  `last_record_at`, `tag_count`), and
  `records: BTreeMap<Uuid, RecordFile>` (with
  `topic`, `tags`, `source`, `created_at`,
  `file_path`, `size_bytes`). Three
  `pub async fn` helpers:
  `load(storage_root) -> LoadOutcome`,
  `save(storage_root, &InMemoryIndex) ->
  Result<(), io::Error>`, and
  `rebuild_from_disk(storage_root) ->
  Result<InMemoryIndex, io::Error>`. The
  `LoadOutcome` enum is
  `Loaded(InMemoryIndex) | Missing | Corrupt
  { reason: String }`. The `save()` helper
  uses the atomic-write pattern (temp file
  in the same directory + rename + parent
  fsync) — same guarantee as the record
  write path. The `rebuild_from_disk()` walker
  is best-effort: it walks every
  `<storage_root>/<topic_slug>/` directory,
  parses the `record_id` from the `.md`
  filename, and rebuilds the in-memory
  `topics` + `tag_index` + `slug_to_topic`
  structures.
- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/tests/adapter_crash_safety.rs` —
  2 tests: (1) `boot_with_corrupt_index_json_rebuilds_from_disk`
  — writes a junk `.index.json` and a valid
  on-disk record, boots, asserts the adapter
  warns and the record is visible;
  (2) `boot_cleans_up_orphan_temp_files` —
  drops 3 `*.md.tmp.<uuid>` files into the
  storage root, boots, asserts they are
  removed.
- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/tests/adapter_concurrency.rs` —
  1 test: `concurrent_store_information_same_topic`
  — 100 parallel `store_information` calls
  (gated by a `tokio::sync::Barrier`), then
  asserts (a) all 100 return `Ok`,
  (b) `find_information` returns all 100
  records, (c) all 100 `RecordId`s are
  unique, (d) the on-disk `.index.json`
  contains all 100 (re-boot, re-verify).
- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/tests/proptest_round_trips.rs` —
  9 `proptest!` properties, 256 cases each:
  `KnowledgeRecord`, `RecordId`,
  `FindInformationRequest`, `FindInformationResponse`,
  `Topic`, `KnowledgeCapabilities`,
  `KnowledgeErrorV1` (all 5 variants via
  `prop_oneof!`), `KnowledgeQueried`,
  `KnowledgeRecordStored`. Each property
  serializes to `serde_json` + back and
  asserts equality.
- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/tests/adapter_events.rs` —
  4 tests:
  (1) `queried_event_does_not_leak_free_text` —
  `find_information` with
  `free_text = "sensitive_query_xyzzy"`,
  assert the captured `KnowledgeQueried`
  event's `serde_json` does not contain
  `"sensitive_query_xyzzy"`.
  (2) `stored_event_does_not_leak_content` —
  `store_information` with content
  `"sensitive_content_xyzzy"`, assert the
  captured `KnowledgeRecordStored` event's
  `serde_json` does not contain that string.
  (3) `queried_event_fires_on_empty_result` —
  `find_information` with no matches still
  publishes one `KnowledgeQueried` event.
  (4) `stored_event_fires_after_index_writes` —
  the adapter only publishes
  `KnowledgeRecordStored` after
  `.index.json` is durable (asserted by
  inspecting the on-disk file before
  subscription receives the event).

**Modified files:**

- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/src/adapter.rs` —
  `store_information` now writes the
  in-memory index to `.index.json` via
  `index_file::save()` after updating the
  in-memory state. `new()` calls
  `index_file::load()` and dispatches on
  the `LoadOutcome`: `Missing` → empty index
  + `tracing::info!`; `Corrupt { reason }` →
  `tracing::warn!` + `rebuild_from_disk()`.
  `read_to_string` failures on a record
  file are now mapped to `MalformedRecord`
  (was `StorageUnavailable`). The
  `content_tokens` cache entry is evicted
  on every `store_information` call.
- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/src/index.rs` —
  `InMemoryIndex` gained the `Debug` derive
  (needed for `LoadOutcome`'s `Debug`).
  `add_record()` signature now takes
  `(input: &KnowledgeRecordInput, slug:
  &str, record_id: RecordId, size_bytes:
  u64)` so the on-disk `RecordFile` has the
  full set of fields it needs.
- `crates/afa-plugin-knowledge-json/src/lib.rs` —
  re-exports the new `index_file` module.

