## Work ethics followed

- Story-telling comments on every
  non-trivial function (the
  "plain English first" rule from
  [PHILOSOPHY.md](file:///home/spanexx/Shared/agents/PHILOSOPHY.md)).
- CID headers on every new type and
  function.
- No fake / tautological tests — every
  test asserts on observable behavior
  (file system state, on-disk `.md`
  files, on-disk `.index.json`, bus
  events, lock-discipline behavior).
- Validation gate is the single-command
  `make` entry point.
- v1 limitations documented inline
  (in the code, in the IMPL doc, in
  this handoff) so the next contributor
  doesn't have to re-derive them.

## Suggested commit message (you run manually)

```
feat(knowledge-engine-json-store): pack #5 phase 3 (resilience) complete

* index_file.rs: IndexFileV1 on-disk format with LoadOutcome
  (Loaded/Missing/Corrupt) + atomic save() + rebuild_from_disk() +
  cleanup_orphan_temp_files().
* adapter.rs: store_information writes .index.json atomically; new()
  dispatches on LoadOutcome (Missing -> empty index, Corrupt -> rebuild
  from disk with tracing::warn); read_to_string failures on record
  files now map to MalformedRecord; content_tokens cache evicted on
  every store_information.
* index.rs: InMemoryIndex gained Debug derive; add_record() signature
  expanded with the fields needed by the on-disk RecordFile.
* Tests: 2 in adapter_crash_safety.rs (corrupt .index.json rebuild +
  orphan temp file cleanup at boot); 1 in adapter_concurrency.rs
  (100 parallel store_information calls, all 100 present in the
  index, no lost writes, no duplicate RecordIds); 9 in
  proptest_round_trips.rs (256 cases per property for all 9 Knowledge
  types); 4 in adapter_events.rs (no free_text in queried event, no
  content in stored event, queried event fires on empty result,
  stored event fires only after index write is durable).
* IMPL: Phase 3 status PENDING -> DONE with full inventory.
* Validation: 342 tests, 0 failed. All 4 gates green.

v1 limitation documented inline: rebuild_from_disk() is best-effort;
the topic name may not be perfectly recovered from the slug alone.
A future pack adds a <record_id>.json metadata sidecar for lossless
recovery.
```

